description.plain:
BIA (birth name Bianca Landrau) is a rapper from Boston. She is also known for being on the reality television show Sisterhood of Hip Hop.

BIA is of Puerto Rican and Italian descent. She wanted to become a rapper at a very young age but only took it seriously after surviving a nearly fatal motorcycle accident.

About her beginning, BIA stated:

When I was young in Boston, probably like 14, I used to hang with a bunch of rappers in the studio. They’re famous battle rappers now. Back then, they were coming up. They used to be in the studio. I used to hit the ‘record’ button for them all the time. I was writing but I didn’t tell anybody until I was 18.

She was discovered by her current manager Famlay through YouTube and was later introduced to Pharrell Williams, who signed her to the i Am Other music label.

In late 2014, she released a mixtape entitled #CHOLASEASON. As she states, her major influences came from rappers like Jay Z, and Puerto-Rican singers like Ivy Queen and Selena.

songs.title: Esta Noche

description.plain:
BIA teams up with Ariana Grande for this latin-infused, hip-hop/trap single.

The two debuted and performed the song together during shows of Grande’s Dangerous Woman Tour, beginning with BIA’s guest performance at the February 19, 2017 concert in Manchester, New Hampshire. BIA appeared at two more shows in the United States and later followed Grande to serve as the opening act for 8 shows on the European leg of the tour.

The song was said to be created for BIA’s debut EP, Trap Vogue, but after pushbacks to the release date, fans have had doubts about whether the track will see the light of day. Rumors have also arisen of the track being scrapped due to alleged copyright issues. Despite this, BIA insists the song will indeed come out eventually.

https://twitter.com/ArianaTodayNet/status/984575653692485633

The song leaked in full via SoundCloud on July 6th, 2018.

songs.title: WHOLE LOTTA MONEY

description.plain:
platinum-certified Boston-born and Los Angeles-based rapper BIA uncovers the music video for her latest single “Whole Lotta Money.” It notably boasts a cameo from Justin Combs. The song remains a standout from her acclaimed 2020 For Certain EP via Epic Records.

Directed by Ben Marc [Ty Dolla $ign, Trey Songz], the clip features BIA in a series of eye-popping vignettes. PAPER Magazine calls BIA “an absolute financial fatale” in the video as she raps by a fire on a plush vintage green couch, takes over kiddie rides with an equally fly girl gang, and saunters through a bodega with Justin Combs behind the counter counting racks. Flexing in designer head-to-toe, she literally brings the lyrics, “I put on my jewelry just to go to the bodega, and I keep it with me just so that I’m feeling safer,” to life. Fittingly, it culminates with bills upon bills raining down in the strip club.

songs.title: Gucci Comin Home

description.plain:
Early on Thursday (May 26), rising Boston rap star BIA was bombarded with text messages and social media alerts, all with one message: Gucci Mane has been freed from prison.

And just like that, the lyrics to her latest single came true.
Back in March, BIA dropped “Gucci Comin Home,” a dedication to rap icon Gucci Mane, who was locked up in 2013 after violating his probation. During his incarceration, several rumors surfaced about GuWop’s release. It was one of those false starts, earlier in the year, which inspired the whole song she told Genius:

 “  I was in the studio just listening through beats with [the song’s producer] Bunx and that beat came on, and the first thing that came to my mind was, ‘Gucci comin’ home, Gucci comin’ home’ because that week I heard Gucci was coming home. We heard he was coming home a couple times, but he didn’t come home.

BIA, who is signed to Pharrell Williams’ i Am Other label, is a big-time Gucci fan and even wrote him a letter last year. It didn’t take her long to write the entire song.

“I write pretty quick so the whole song probably took an hour or two,” she said.
The track, which has a beat that sounds like an ice cream truck, also features some pretty clever lines like: “Man, if Gucci comin’ home then we don’t need no Donald Trump.”

“He’s the hood president, he’s the street’s president, so we don’t need no Donald Trump,” BIA said when asked about the line.

OK, so maybe GuWop won’t actually run for the presidency, but at least he has some cool campaign music.

description.plain:
COOKIE is an upcoming collaboration between rappers BIA and Iggy Azalea included on the Deluxe Version of BIA’s sophomore EP due to be released before Summer.

Rumours about a possible collaboration between the two spread around December, 2020 when BIA tweeted that she wanted Iggy on the official Remix of her hit song “COVER GIRL”.



 The Remix never came to fruition though due to Iggy’s tight schedule while finishing her third studio album instead the two decided on a new song for the Deluxe repackaging of the EP.

The song was first teased by Iggy on Twitter on March 24, 2021. https://twitter.com/IGGYAZALEA/status/1374665784996159495?s=20 BIA -confirmed the title on April 24, 2021. https://twitter.com/biabia/status/1386011125163208704?s=21
